  <section id="built-on" class="builton section">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="builton__head" data-reveal>
        <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--accent">Built on</span>
        <h2 class="h2 builton__title">First-party frameworks, end to end.</h2>
        <p class="lead builton__intro">No cross-platform runtime sits between blau and the OS. Every screen is native, and the hard parts lean on the tools Apple ships its own platforms on.</p>
      </header>

      <ul class="builton__grid" data-reveal style="--delay:60ms">
        <li class="builton__cell">
          <span class="builton__name builton__name--mark">Ghostty / libghostty</span>
          <span class="builton__role">GPU-accelerated, Metal-rendered terminal engine, embedded via GhosttyKit.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="builton__cell">
          <span class="builton__name builton__name--mark">WhisperKit</span>
          <span class="builton__role">On-device Whisper speech-to-text on Apple Silicon via Core ML. MIT-licensed.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="builton__cell">
          <span class="builton__name builton__name--mark">Network.framework</span>
          <span class="builton__role">NWListener / NWBrowser / NWConnection for the peer-to-peer media transport.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="builton__cell">
          <span class="builton__name">MultipeerConnectivity</span>
          <span class="builton__role">Encrypted MCSession control channel between Mac, iPhone, and Watch.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="builton__cell">
          <span class="builton__name">ScreenCaptureKit</span>
          <span class="builton__role">Captures Pilot's window as IOSurface-backed frames for the live mirror.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="builton__cell">
          <span class="builton__name builton__name--mark">VideoToolbox</span>
          <span class="builton__role">Hardware HEVC encode and decode on the dedicated media engine.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="builton__cell">
          <span class="builton__name">Swift 6 + SwiftUI</span>
          <span class="builton__role">Strict concurrency catches data races at compile time, across all four apps.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="builton__cell">
          <span class="builton__name">SwiftData</span>
          <span class="builton__role">Persists workspaces, panes, browser state, and notes with the @Model macro.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="builton__cell">
          <span class="builton__name">PencilKit</span>
          <span class="builton__role">Low-latency Apple Pencil annotation on Plotter, synced back to the Mac.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="builton__cell">
          <span class="builton__name">WidgetKit + ActivityKit</span>
          <span class="builton__role">Plotter's Home Screen widget and Dynamic Island Live Activity.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="builton__cell">
          <span class="builton__name">WatchConnectivity</span>
          <span class="builton__role">Wingman &#8644; Copilot messaging for the double-pinch gesture.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="builton__cell">
          <span class="builton__name">XcodeGen</span>
          <span class="builton__role">Generates the Xcode project from a declarative YAML spec.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="builton__closing mono" data-reveal style="--delay:120ms">SwiftUI &middot; Swift 6.0 &middot; macOS / iOS / watchOS / iPadOS</p>
    </div>
  </section>

